member.name: FILE_IN_CABINET_INFO
member.summary: TheFILE_IN_CABINET_INFO structure provides information about a file found in the cabinet. The function sends this structure as one of the parameters when it sends aSPFILENOTIFY_FILEINCABINET notification to the cabinet callback routine.

member.name: FILE_IN_CABINET_INFO.NameInCabinet
member.summary: File name as it exists within the cabinet file.

member.name: FILE_IN_CABINET_INFO.FileSize
member.summary: Uncompressed size of the file in the cabinet, in bytes.

member.name: FILE_IN_CABINET_INFO.Win32Error
member.summary: If an error occurs, this member is the system error code. If no error has occurred, it is NO_ERROR.

member.name: FILE_IN_CABINET_INFO.DosDate
member.summary: Date that the file was last saved.

member.name: FILE_IN_CABINET_INFO.DosTime
member.summary: MS-DOS time stamp of the file in the cabinet.

member.name: FILE_IN_CABINET_INFO.DosAttribs
member.summary: Attributes of the file in the cabinet.
